wait did we fuck up their projector or no

OK, talked to Eric Scifres, in addition to what we're doing they want us to zero in on how one would utilize a phone or a tablet to create training content. Think Lego Super Hero Movie Maker meets Burgertime. We can explain this as lo-fi as we want, in sketches or pictures. They're envisioning this as 1-2 screens of product UI and some setup wherein the "main chef" and "cameraperson" collaborate to shoot, annotate, and share out training content. He was pretty prescriptive in what this process would look like "so, they'd film something, then pause, and annotate the video, then shoot again, then pause," etc. but then gave us the magical four words: "you're the creative people." The point of this is to show Japan their process, so that they can understand this specific element.
